<a name="Test Toggles">
<h3>
2.6.3  Test Toggles
</h3>
</a>
<p>
When a teacher is ready to allow students to take a test,
he/she can come to this option and turn the switch on
for the desired test
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Figure Initial screen">
<a name="Initial screen">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/toggle1.jpg" height="400" width="550">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 1:  Initial screen.  </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

The initial screen when clicked into the toggle page will contain a list of 
classes you are teaching. This option allows us to separate tests by classes so 
it will be more organized in the future.

<p>
Figure 2 shows turn the toggle on

<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Figure Expanded menus tab">
<a name="Expanded menus tab">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/toggle2.jpg" height="400" width="550">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 2:  Turn Toggles On  </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p> Click on the desired class that teacher would like to have test in.

<p> Follows the click, there will be a drop down of created tests.
<p> On the right hand side, there will be a switch. When bar is green, it means the test is live, if it is grey, the test is off.
